						               													<description>From the publisher:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;A Four Player Abstract Strategy Game with Goblins&amp;quot;&amp;#10;Comprises a leather board 15&amp;quot; x 15&amp;quot; and wooden pieces; all hand-finished. Each player controls an army of Giants, Ogres, Trolls, Dwarves, Hobgoblins and Goblins, battling for land in the prized turnip-growing valley of Ogre's Knee.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start the four armies are positioned at the corners of the board. The initial aim of the armies, of which each constituent has a different numerical value, is to capture opposing pieces. Capture is custodial, captors having to have a higher combined value than those being captured. Players can combine in capture. Capture is rewarded by gold, which, when sufficient has accumulated, allows an army to build a monument. Further gold allows players to build walls around the territory they dominate, enclosing both men and monument.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The primary aim of the Battle is to capture territory on the board; and the winner is the player who captures and encloses the largest territory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
